init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The 92nd little pig said, "no, I don't want to sell it to the Russians.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was like, "dude, I'm a wolf.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The 92nd little pig said, "no, I have not heard that phrase.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The 92nd little pig was a very patriotic pig.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He went to the local police station and said, "I want to report a wolf."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So they sent the 92nd little pig to the FBI.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The FBI took that kind of thing very seriously.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: When the wolf got to the little pig's house, the FBI was already there.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I was just going to tell the little pig that he shouldn't build his house out of depleted uranium!"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The 92nd little pig was very pleased with himself.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the townspeople were very proud of him.
